-- KeyCorp Hires Mark Williams From PNC Financial for Lead Management Team
-- Laura Keeley
-- 2010-07-01T14:27:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/keycorp-hires-mark-williams-from-pnc-financial-for-lead-management-team.html

          
          
             KeyCorp , Ohio’s second-largest
lender, hired Mark Williams from  PNC Financial Services Group
Inc.  for the new position of corporate strategy director.  
 Williams, a former aerospace engineer, will report to Chief
Executive Officer  Henry L. Meyer III , the Cleveland-based
company said today in a statement. He will lead the bank’s
strategic planning and be an adviser to KeyCorp’s clients,
according to the statement.  
 Williams is a graduate of Harvard Business School and the
Polytechnic Institute of New York University, where he earned a
bachelor’s degree in aerospace engineering. He worked for
General Electric Aircraft Engines and  Capital One Financial
Corp . before overseeing several PNC corporate-banking units,
including global banking.  
